:"text","text":" refers to things such as cash on hand, inventories, raw materials, loans to suppliers, and payments from customers—the grease that keeps the wheels of production moving. We will discuss working capital in more detail in ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"aaf802dc-a693-442a-8c6c-d55201e86253","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 2","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"e992f9c0-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" and devote all of ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"95830ba3-9b7b-4514-954e-e8e586fa91e7","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 19","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"7be44040-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" to working capital management.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"5","marks":[]}],"object":"inline","type":"footnote","ref":"44339f82-358b-496c-af47-12627b4696e4"},{"object":"text","text":" may seem straightforward, but in a young or growing company, it can mean the difference between success and failure. Even companies with great products require a lot of money to develop and bring those products to market. Consider the costs to Starbucks of launching their VIA instant coffee, which included developing the instant coffee crystals and creating a big marketing campaign for them, or the costs to Boeing of producing the 787—billions of dollars were spent before the first 787 finally left the ground in December 2009. A company typically burns through a significant amount of cash before the sales of the product generate income. The financial manager’s job is to make sure that limited access to cash does not hinder the firm’s success.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"5a55e38b-8abd-4d25-bd3f-9f188bb5ac93"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","